      About this item

      • Millions of Color Options: Select from 16 million colors and 1-100% dimmable brightness to fill large spaces with 1000 lumens of bright light and improve safety on stairs and hallways. Includes tunable 2700k-6500k warm white to cool daylight options.
      • Flexible Connectivity: These smart retrofit recessed downlights support Wi-Fi and Bluetooth direct control for more convenience. The connectivity options allow a more stable connection, unlike those that only support Wi-Fi or Bluetooth.
      • Easy Installation: Quickly install the 6-inch LED Retrofit Downlights into existing cans and pull power from the recessed can by connecting an E26 to a TP24 connector. These can lights will slip into 6'' cans and secure with spring clips.
      • Multiple Scene Modes: Access an exciting variety of 65 preset scene modes inspired by nature, holidays, and more on Govee Home App. There is also a selection of fun music modes that match up with your favorite music (Govee Music Sync Box Required).
      • All-In-One Group Control: There is no need to change the colors or brightness manually. Use the Group Control feature to control all your lights using the app. You can also adjust the lights in separate rooms by making them separate groups.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Govee Lights: The Extra $20 I Should’ve Spent from the Start
        Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2024
        Color: 4 PackSize: 6 InchVerified Purchase
        In 2023, we rebuilt my grandparents’ home and moved in just before Thanksgiving. For the lighting, I grabbed 25 Lumary 6" Retrofit Can Lights because, hey, they were cheaper than Govee. Big mistake. Within the first month, three lights went haywire—one started blinking dimly in random colors, and others just straight-up lost connection. Over the next few months, I replaced somewhere between five and eight of them. Lumary even offered me a full refund as a goodwill gesture, but (surprise) they never followed through. Long story short: you get what you pay for.

        Sick of the constant issues, I replaced one room with Govee lights, and wow—I wish I’d just spent the extra $20 per set upfront. These lights are flawless. No connection problems, no random glitches—just reliable, bright, beautiful lighting. The range of colors is incredible, and they connect instantly to Wi-Fi and Bluetooth. Plus, the Govee app is super intuitive and plays perfectly with my Alexa system.

        Since making the switch, I’ve gone all-in with Govee. I’ve added bulbs for lamps in the living room, my son’s bedroom, and even strip lights in random spots. Their TV lights? Absolute game-changer. Syncing them with the TV creates an immersive experience that’s hard to beat. And the Govee app? It’s regularly updated, easy to use, and often has sales or coupons, which is a nice bonus.

        If you’re trying to decide, take it from me—just spend the extra money and go with Govee. I’ve seen people mention issues, but Govee’s customer support is top-notch. They respond quickly and actually replace faulty products. If you’ve had problems with Govee before, I’d encourage you to give them another shot—they’ve totally transformed my home lighting setup.

      • Luis
        5.0 out of 5 stars Great lights
        Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
        Color: 4 PackSize: 6 InchVerified Purchase
        I have used Govee light strips for my TVs in the past and they worked great so when it came time to update my living room lights which used retro fittings I thought why not get color changing ones to help set the mood for movies. Upon seeing these I jumped on the purchase since they were at a good price compared to more expensive ones from other brands.

        Install was very easy literally unscrewed the old led retro lights which used metal clips to hold them in place so seeing that these govee ones used a metal fin I was a bit skeptical that they would hold in place but since the install I’ve had them in a few weeks now and neither of them look like they are falling out at all, I even tug on them every now and again but they are very secured in place so just follow the instructions and you will be fine.

        Adding the lights on the app was very easy thanks to how Govee designed the app, adjusting the colors are also easy and you can even group them together to make simultaneous adjustments at the same time. The only thing I will add that is a bit annoying is that the lights tend to lose wifi connection so it takes a few seconds for them to come up on the app again which delays being able to adjust the lights but a minor inconvenience.

        Over all I’m happy with these lights and I may look into purchasing another set for another room.

        Adding the lights on the app was very easy thanks to how Govee designed the app, adjusting the colors are also easy and you can even group them together to make simultaneous adjustments at the same time. The only thing I will add that is a bit annoying is that the lights tend to lose wifi connection so it takes a few seconds for them to come up on the app again which delays being able to adjust the lights but a minor inconvenience.

        Over all I’m happy with these lights and I may look into purchasing another set for another room.
